                    <div class="section-header">
                        <h2 class="text-center">What is a Calendar?</h2>
                        <p>A calendar is a chart or device which displays the date and the day of the week, and often the whole of a particular year divided up into months, weeks, and days.</p>
			<p>A calendar can also mean a list of planned events, such as a schedule calendar, class calendar, or to-do list calendar...</p>
			<p>The most common type of pre-modern calendar was the lunisolar calendar, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lunar_calendar">a lunar calendar</a> that occasionally adds one intercalary month to remain synchronized with the solar year over the long term.</p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="section-header">
                        <h2 class="text-center">Why people need a Calendar?</h2>
			<p>Calendars have been around for thousands of years. We all know it can help you keep track of social events, appointments, meetings. The benefit of time management is obvious. What is not obvious is that calendars have the potential to help manage your stress, your wellbeing as well as your activities.</p>
			<p>Lots of people are using online calendars today. But there are some valid reasons you may still want <strong>a printable calendar</strong> such as wall calendar, schedule calendar, <a href="photo">photo calendar</a>.</p>

			<ul>
			<li><strong>Quick Visual Reminder</strong>: If you want to keep track of personal and business schedules then a paper calendar is better than online calendar. Put it over the desk at home or office and serves as a quick visual reminder.</li>

			<li><strong>Remember Events Better</strong>: When you have to write down meetings and other important appointments you’ll be more likely to remember them. It can also help bring to mind other significant details about your schedule. You don’t have to forget a single event or meeting with help.</li>

			<li><strong>Planning Sessions</strong>: It’s easy to add notes, meetings, and appointments in your calendar. Highlight items of importance or use different colors to denote different recurring events.</li>


			<li><strong>Tracking Family Activities</strong>: Using a calendar at home are helpful. By entering all the kids activities; their different sporting events, band practices and social activities, as a parent, you will be able to stay on top of household schedules.</li>


			<li><strong>Schedule out your days</strong>: You can schedule out every hour of your day if you are having problems with time management. This practice empowers you to precisely know what you need to be doing and when.</li>


			<li><strong>Deciding on Meals</strong>: Record everything on your calendar to keep track your meals. This way you don’t get stuck in a rut serving the same things week after week.</li>

			</ul>


